---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Nuku | Seba Sepulveda">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-3xl py-16">
    <a href="/projects" class="mb-8 inline-block text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-yellow-400 transition-colors">
      &lt;- Back to projects
    </a>

    <header class="mb-10">
      <div class="mb-3 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
        <span class="rounded-full border border-rose-500/30 px-2 py-0.5 text-xs text-rose-400">Active</span>
        <span class="rounded-full border border-rose-500/30 px-2 py-0.5 text-xs text-rose-400">Local-first</span>
        <span class="rounded-full border border-rose-500/30 px-2 py-0.5 text-xs text-rose-400">Self-hosted</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Nuku</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-300">
        A local-first, self-hosted health tracker for families that need to record and review blood pressure, glucose and insulin measurements for multiple patients.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Why it exists</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        Nuku is built around a common family-care workflow: several relatives may need to help track health measurements for one or more people, often from a phone, without sending sensitive data to a third-party cloud service.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-300">
        The product focuses on private infrastructure, clear daily summaries and low-friction data entry rather than social features or analytics that require centralizing personal health data.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What it does</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
        <li>Tracks blood pressure, glucose and insulin records for multiple patients.</li>
        <li>Shows daily summaries and historical trend charts.</li>
        <li>Exports records to Excel for medical appointments or family review.</li>
        <li>Runs as a self-hosted app with PostgreSQL and Docker Compose.</li>
        <li>Includes an optional Telegram bot for quick mobile input.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Technical shape</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-800 p-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Application</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Next.js, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui and Recharts.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-800 p-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Data</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">PostgreSQL, Prisma ORM, Zod validation and shared domain packages.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-800 p-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Automation</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Optional Telegram bot with guided commands for common health records.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-800 p-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Deployment</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Self-hosted Docker Compose workflow designed to keep data under user control.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Live app</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a
          href="https://health-trackerweb-production.up.railway.app/dashboard"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-block rounded-lg border border-rose-500/40 px-4 py-2 text-sm text-rose-300 hover:bg-rose-500/10 transition-colors"
        >
          Open Nuku on Railway
        </a>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-500">
        Deployed on Railway. Examples and articles should use demo or anonymized data only.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Planned articles</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
        <li>Building a local-first health tracker for families.</li>
        <li>Designing multi-patient health records without sending data to the cloud.</li>
        <li>Using Telegram as an optional input channel for caregiver workflows.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
